  "transcript": [
    {
      "start": 1.23,
      "end": 3416.46,
      "text": "The Friday Rock Show with Tommy Vance. Featuring sessions and tracks from artists including AC, Motörhead, Syd Barrett, Frank Zappa, Bad Company, Pretenders, Todd Rundgren. This is Tommy Vance on Radio 1."
    },
    {
      "start": 3416.48,
      "end": 3420.4,
      "text": "Also Tim, that's Tim Barker"
    },
    {
      "start": 3420.4,
      "end": 3422.82,
      "text": "of 2 Gibraltar Avenue, Brompton, Gillingham and Kent"
    },
    {
      "start": 3422.82,
      "end": 3425.32,
      "text": "says, play that record for Pez"
    },
    {
      "start": 3425.32,
      "end": 3427.74,
      "text": "and Ian and Nick and Ivy and Gem and Mike"
    },
    {
      "start": 3427.74,
      "end": 3429.8,
      "text": "and everybody else who likes it"
    },
    {
      "start": 3429.8,
      "end": 3436.07,
      "text": "Oh, that's also for Carol of Derbyshire"
    },
    {
      "start": 3436.07,
      "end": 3439.08,
      "text": "from Lowry of Stockport"
    },
    {
      "start": 3439.08,
      "end": 3442.1,
      "text": "wishing her a very happy 21st birthday"
    },
    {
      "start": 3442.1,
      "end": 3443.02,
      "text": "which is coming soon"
    },
    {
      "start": 3443.02,
      "end": 3448.92,
      "text": "And for Paul, led to Boltwood"
    },
    {
      "start": 3448.92,
      "end": 3452.2,
      "text": "of Elm Park, Hornchurch and Essex"
    },
    {
      "start": 3452.2,
      "end": 3460.55,
      "text": "It's an astonishing bit of music, really, that Leonard Skinner track."
    },
    {
      "start": 3460.61,
      "end": 3462.41,
      "text": "It just never, ever seems to date."
    },
    {
      "start": 3462.53,
      "end": 3464.41,
      "text": "You can play it time after time after time,"
    },
    {
      "start": 3464.47,
      "end": 3466.67,
      "text": "and it sounds just as fresh every time you hear it."
    },
    {
      "start": 3467.23,
      "end": 3468.91,
      "text": "Here's our last one by the Handsome Beasts."
    },
    {
      "start": 3469.13,
      "end": 3470.39,
      "text": "It's called Another Day."
    },
    {
      "start": 3989.13,
      "end": 3989.89,
      "text": "Handsome Beasts."
    },
    {
      "start": 3989.99,
      "end": 3991.89,
      "text": "Steve Howell on the bass, Phil Aston on guitar,"
    },
    {
      "start": 3992.17,
      "end": 3995.67,
      "text": "Pete Malbasa on the drums, and Gary Dalloway on vocals."
    },
    {
      "start": 3996.31,
      "end": 3998.18,
      "text": "That was called Another Day."
    },
    {
      "start": 4001.67,
      "end": 4002.45,
      "text": "What about Another Day?"
    },
    {
      "start": 4002.45,
      "end": 4005.29,
      "text": "On Rock On Tomorrow, you can hear John Anderson and Van Gillis"
    },
    {
      "start": 4005.29,
      "end": 4006.91,
      "text": "talking about their current album."
    },
    {
      "start": 4006.91,
      "end": 4009.67,
      "text": "The rock on is on the air between 5 and 6.30."
    },
    {
      "start": 4010.05,
      "end": 4012.25,
      "text": "Thanks to Neil and his compatriot tonight,"
    },
    {
      "start": 4012.39,
      "end": 4014.63,
      "text": "whose name I can't remember, but thank you very much, Wicca Tom."
    },
    {
      "start": 4016.15,
      "end": 4017.17,
      "text": "Oh, Nick. Thank you, Nick."
    },
    {
      "start": 4017.83,
      "end": 4018.99,
      "text": "Young Nick, not old Nick."
    },
    {
      "start": 4019.82,
      "end": 4021.2,
      "text": "Talking about old. Wilson?"
    },
    {
      "start": 4021.78,
      "end": 4023.1,
      "text": "Yeah, well, I don't know about you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 4023.18,
      "end": 4024.84,
      "text": "but I'm going to go do a bit of swimming tomorrow"
    },
    {
      "start": 4024.84,
      "end": 4026.16,
      "text": "and see if I can lose a few pounds."
    },
    {
      "start": 4026.44,
      "end": 4027.16,
      "text": "Down the middle."
    },
    {
      "start": 4029.22,
      "end": 4031.46,
      "text": "Well, tomorrow night, I'm going to swim all the way to Malta, mate."
    },
    {
      "start": 4031.82,
      "end": 4032.58,
      "text": "White snake, yeah?"
    },
    {
      "start": 4032.76,
      "end": 4033.54,
      "text": "Yeah, white snake."
    },
    {
      "start": 4034.08,
      "end": 4035.46,
      "text": "Good one. Good one next week."
    },
    {
      "start": 4037.41,
      "end": 4037.87,
      "text": "That's it."
    },
    {
      "start": 4037.87,
      "end": 4039.59,
      "text": "wherever you are"
    },
    {
      "start": 4039.59,
      "end": 4040.99,
      "text": "try to stay out of trouble"
    },
    {
      "start": 4040.99,
      "end": 4043.0,
      "text": "and God bless"
    },
    {
      "start": 4043.0,
      "end": 4043.72,
      "text": "goodnight"
    }
  ]
}